Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you turn the voice down?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.06,0:02:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the energy was very strong this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.78,0:02:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual energy is too much for the human nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.25,0:02:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more comfortable to stay stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just get in there and fight and kill and have a hell of a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We realize, those of you who have been here before,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:03:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The primary illusion to get over is that there is anything causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe in causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be unable to disidentify with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will presume there is a this called an I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.53,0:03:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,causing a that called actions or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.12,0:03:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The fastest way to make rapid spiritual progress is to meditate and realize
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.34,0:03:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is occurring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As a natural consequence, there is an infinite field of power similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say, to gravity and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,within that field responds to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.09,0:03:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.47,0:03:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, these two things are moving within the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of this moving this way is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.68,0:04:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of this moving this way is the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.28,0:04:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not causing that to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.40,0:04:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every word that is spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.08,0:04:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's being spoken until I hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.68,0:04:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask me, what am I going to talk about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.92,0:04:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We make up things because the audience wants to know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If I told him the truth, how many would come?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he doesn't know what he's going to be talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.48,0:04:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.37,0:04:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can't handle reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we make up fictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.86,0:04:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we'll talk about truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.48,0:05:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God manifests as creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is what seems to perception to be a progressive unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.19,0:05:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there isn't any unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But that makes people happy to tell them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.55,0:05:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stopwatch is your point of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.26,0:05:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Each movement arises out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Each movement arises out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This movement did not arise out of this movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This movement did not arise out of this movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.72,0:05:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, this movement arose spontaneously out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, this movement arose spontaneously out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.83,0:06:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And this movement arises out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.83,0:06:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this movement arises out of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.27,0:06:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.27,0:06:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that intention and the presence of an infinite power called divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.27,0:06:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that intention and the presence of an infinite power called divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.27,0:06:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then appears forth as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.52,0:06:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then appears forth as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.72,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,every word spoken this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is the effulgence of creation as it appears
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to get beyond the idea of cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.25,0:06:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,cause and effect is a calibrated energy field at 460
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.69,0:06:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that means it's an intellectualization
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where's our wonderful map
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.23,0:06:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what would we do without our map, we'd be screwed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.26,0:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, reason, evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution about 450
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,causality about 460
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.37,0:07:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics about 460
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.58,0:07:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.14,0:07:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but they have no basis in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.43,0:07:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective experiential reality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.35,0:07:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,they're abstractions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is causing anything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.26,0:07:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and if nothing is causing anything
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then evolution is a limited concept as you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.55,0:07:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if everything we've said so far is true
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we've said so far is true
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.25,0:07:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.63,0:07:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and so evolution has brought us to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.18,0:07:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,where the first time in all of human history
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.32,0:07:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a means of discerning truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.67,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that is such a staggering realization
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the first person that I'd shared my work with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who I sent it to him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,took off two weeks and went to Europe to get over the shock
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he said it totally blew everything I'd ever believed in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.08,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he said it totally blew everything I'd ever believed in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,totally recontextualized my whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.91,0:08:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so it took me 30 years to even approach the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for 30 years the presence within
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was never spoken of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing you can say about it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the 90s arose a means of explaining spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in ways that are definable and describable and verifiable
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.03,0:08:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so then that came about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as a means of explaining spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the writing of power versus force
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.92,0:09:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the impact of that information is overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.23,0:09:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of like the discovery of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.47,0:09:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or the computer chip or the compass
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.32,0:09:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the telescope, the microscope
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.37,0:09:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was a new instant with which to examine
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,everything mankind believes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or has believed throughout history
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a way of discovering that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.44,0:09:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,just think in the middle ages
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.90,0:09:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where the black people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,plague wiped out like half of Europe or something. They didn't even know it was germs. They didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.73,0:09:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,know it was germs. They didn't know it was bad air, wicked people, all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.72,0:09:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody discovered germs. There wasn't any microscope. So the discovery of the microscope
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:10:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,totally revolutionized human life. We don't die of great plagues anymore. So an instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood then reveals things that are somewhat shocking and quite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.23,0:10:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,dissimilar to common human belief. If common human belief was credible, we wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.89,0:10:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the problems that we have today. Consequently, what people believe and their opinions are
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,worth nothing. That's the happy news. Everybody is free and entitled to be wrong, and they
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So all we're saying is that the plague is not caused by bad air, darkness, leaving the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:11:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,windows open or shut. The plague is caused by a bacillus. Oh, boy. To discover anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,new usually subjects you to a good deal of hostility from large quarters. And some of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.28,0:11:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that we'll say this morning I'm sure will do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.65,0:11:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is occurring spontaneously of its own, just like the discovery of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,microscope, how to tell truth from falsehood. It was a spontaneous discovery, a sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,like realization. It happened in a flash. A tenth of a second I saw it instantly. And
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then when we begin to apply it to common human problems, we get a different viewpoint of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.40,0:11:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what the problem is all about. And so before we can solve a problem, what the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a problem, we first have to be able to define it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In medicine, we call that diagnosis. So this morning we'll do some diagnostic work, and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.37,0:12:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we would start with one that's quite prominent in the world today. Before we do
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.78,0:12:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that, however, there's a gentleman in the audience who I have challenged to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.10,0:12:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to do this correctly, I have to have a gentleman. Come up, gentleman. Has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.75,0:12:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a bona fide gentleman. And in my bag is something you're going to need to see. And the gentleman,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.58,0:12:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the gentleman will stand there, and I will stand here. You're going to need that. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:13:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to have a duel. You stand here, Susie, and wear your thing. All right. When
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,she goes like this, do a practice. She does the white scarf, we will, bang! We'll practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.78,0:13:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang! So we will keep our gun store aside, and when Susie gives us the go-ahead, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.19,0:13:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,see if we can kill each other. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready, Susie?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.41,0:13:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready with it. Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.41,0:13:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.61,0:13:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.61,0:13:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we're going to have a fight with the daggers. But here, you come over here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.00,0:14:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,back up this way. Okay. All right. Now, this way. Now we will take four steps forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then turn and fight. Okay? Go! Okay, let's put War and Peace up. Now that we've gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.57,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,rid of that stupid thing, we're going to do the next one. We're going to do the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.29,0:14:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand the causes of war. Peace is the natural state when truth prevails, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.75,0:14:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,war is the state when falsehood prevails. So the opposite of peace is not war. The opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:15:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of peace is falsehood. To eliminate falsehood, you have no war. That's why the propagators
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.79,0:15:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsehood are so vociferous. That looks a little fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.37,0:15:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we keep ringing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,War and Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.46,0:15:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So peace is not something you can cause. Peace parades don't cause peace. Everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for peace. You know what I'm saying? Peace parades are dangerous. They're too dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to. I don't want to go to a peace demonstration. There's dogs, police, people knocking each
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.62,0:15:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,other over the head, being dragged off to jail. It's violent. Peace demonstrations
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.37,0:16:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are too violent for me. I don't want anything to do with them. You're safer in your regiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer in your regiment than you are in a peace demonstration. Nobody's getting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.82,0:16:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you with clubs arresting you. There's no dogs biting your legs. The basis of war is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.54,0:16:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance, and the basic problem is that men cannot tell truth from falsehood. The consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.41,0:16:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,politically is that because they cannot tell truth from falsehood, the populace cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.66,0:16:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,tell a leader from a megalomaniac. The same phenomena happens over and over and over. If
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't Genghis Khan, it's Caesar or Napoleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:16:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Or Hitler or Mussolini or Hirohito. It's one megalomaniac after another. The basic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.17,0:17:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,problem is that people worship a political leader instead of God. Your allegiance is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,due only to God. Therefore, to pledge allegiance to the Fuhrer or to the State or to Saddam
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,or anybody else already puts you in a non-integrist condition. Those who worship anything but
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,God are below 200, because that is a basic falsehood. You cannot be integrist and worship
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.94,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is secular. You can pursue it. You can even reverence money. Holy money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we're going to get to business later today. It's a tough day. Today we're starting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.74,0:17:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with war and we're ending up with business, and then we're getting on to science, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:17:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.74,0:18:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday, the citizens have no capacity to tell truth from falsehood. Therefore, they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.00,0:18:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are easily propagandized. Why? Because of the intrinsic, the trap for mankind is the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.29,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,intrinsic innocence of consciousness. As we've described before, the nature of the human
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is like a computer. The basic consciousness is like the hardware of the computer. You
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,can program anything into it, and the ego, then, is all the software that's been programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,into it. Forgive them, for they know not what they do is a fact. They don't know what they're
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.75,0:18:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,doing. If they think they're honoring God by killing innocent citizens, we say how pathetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't know any better. Okay. So, we come out with compassion, then. If somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.23,0:19:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,kills you out of some mistaken belief, you bless them. You say, brother, you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.23,0:19:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to die. You bless them. You say, brother, I forgive you, right? And thank you for taking
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.39,0:19:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,me out of this vale of tears. Okay. So, innocence is easily programmed into polarized ego positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As Goebbels was the master of that, I once calibrated him. He was like 40 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.76,0:19:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But what he documented is if you repeat a lie often enough, you program people, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they will believe the lie, no matter how outrageous it is. Leave everything and go out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.59,0:19:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,desert, and the UFOs will pick you up. They do that. Thousands of the time. Okay. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.88,0:19:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a different way now. Let's remove all opinion. The way to enlightenment is not
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.49,0:20:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,through opinionation. I guarantee that. It's through divine stupidity. When you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitation of the mind, you see, the mind can only know about something. It cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,know anything. To know anything, you have to be it. The only thing in my household that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,knows a cat is my cat. I can know about the cat, and over time, we learn more about cats,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.71,0:20:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but only kitty knows kitty. No. To know, you have to be that. The world that we talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the world of science and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of politics and the daily newspaper. All these opinions. On the one side, we hear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:21:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the doves, and on the other side, the wolves. What is it? Doves and eagles, foxes, eagles
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.79,0:21:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and hawks. Eagles and hawks. Okay. No, no, not eagles and hawks. Doves and hawks. You
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.84,0:21:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,have the doves. If you don't vote for peace, I'll kill you. Okay. And you got the hawks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.57,0:21:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them. Throughout the lectures, we've shown how the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,world evolves out of animal instincts. What you see is a display of animal nature as it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.33,0:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is acted out within the human domain. Territoriality being one of it. Major ones, dominance, the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.19,0:22:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,dominant cat fighting for territoriality. So, the daily headlines are not much different
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.05,0:22:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,than the wilds of Africa or 40 million years ago. You just see one species fighting for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.85,0:22:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,more space. And mating opportunities. They seem to be obsessed with mating. And food
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and dominance. And therefore, you kill anything that invades your space. In 40 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.81,0:22:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,however, things change. Not much, huh? Oh, God. We don't have fur. That's one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.75,0:22:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,main distinctions between us people. Just a little fur. Not much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.83,0:22:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, let's say we don't know anything about this world. We come from some other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.09,0:22:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,star. And we say, let's study what these people are all about. And the only instrument we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,have is a way to tell truth from false, other than that we don't know anything about these
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.81,0:23:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,people here. So, what happens if we calibrate? Let's put opinion aside. You can save your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.57,0:23:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,booze for later and your cheers for later. The doves and the hawks can take turns. Doves
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.22,0:23:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then hawks. I'm going to do it that way. Okay. If we just calibrate, let's say we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.41,0:23:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,care about personalities. President Bush's address to the Congress, the annual address
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.50,0:23:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was 460. Secretary Powell's position in all this war, and this is 460. The Secretary of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.75,0:23:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Defense is 460. The U.S. military, 450. The U.S. military, 460. The U.S. military, 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.14,0:24:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. State Department, 450. That's their intention. The solicitude for the unintended
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.50,0:24:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,victims of all this, the reluctance to take, even have it happen. So, in the mid-400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.89,0:24:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the mid-400s is about the highest you can expect in ordinary life. The presidency of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.18,0:24:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the United States calibrates around 450 to 460. So, whoever fills that void is going
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.66,0:24:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a different role than whatever the circumstances. This is the level of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.22,0:24:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason, meaning, wisdom, beginning of wisdom. The Supreme Court calibrates about 480. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.50,0:24:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this has to do with reason, logic, thinking a thing through, understanding, the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.25,0:24:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to abstract concepts, ethics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.75,0:25:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 460 is the rule of ethics, reason, balance, doing the intelligent, expected thing, and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.10,0:25:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilling one's obligations. I do a lot of radio programs and they tend to be quite polarized
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.09,0:25:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,politically. And they always get mad when they say, well, what does President Bush calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.09,0:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at? Well, he calibrates at 460. Oh, that can't be. Everybody's mad at that. The presidency
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.34,0:25:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States, to get there and to handle it, you better be around 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.34,0:25:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't handle it otherwise. The high 500s, you'd be out of it. In the high 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.30,0:25:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be able to handle all that, power brokering and detail and all. So, the ideal
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.55,0:25:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,president, the ideal president at this time would be around 460. That would be ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.55,0:26:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the highest president we've ever had was 499. To be able to handle it all, you've
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.56,0:26:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be around 460. The Supreme Court calibrates at 480. The Supreme Court is not on the firing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.18,0:26:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,line. They're into philosophizing and intellect and reason and learnedness. It's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.36,0:26:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,bit too academic at 480 to be president of the United States. You can't be that academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.36,0:26:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be able to relate to the people. You can't be too high or you become sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,ivory tower intellectualism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.06,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'd say, actually, that's pretty ideal. All right. The Congress itself is at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States population has been at 431. I didn't recalibrate it. The U.S. media has
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.94,0:26:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a different mission at 320. The 400s are a little bit too intellectual for the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.25,0:27:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're going to do a TV show, you've got to bring it down to closer to the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.25,0:27:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happened to the – oh. Okay. The U.S. media is around 320. In the new book
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing, we've calibrated all the networks and network news and all the commentators
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.01,0:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and Time and Newsweek and calibrated all the major media. It's like we have a new instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.43,0:27:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with which to study civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.43,0:27:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.43,0:27:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what this new book is about, studying every aspect of human civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.55,0:27:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,from its early onset to its present presentations, everything included, from the Polk to the Dixie
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.42,0:27:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.90,0:28:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the media has to be – you can't be too erudite, and you'll notice that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look at the editorial page.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.85,0:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.79,0:28:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In this whole thing that's going on, we have the peace vigils. As I said, peace protest
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.85,0:28:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,parades calibrate pretty low. But peace vigils are 305, and 300 is goodwill. Goodwill, willingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.08,0:28:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it's benign. A peace vigil is benign. It threatens no one. We're supposed to have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.33,0:28:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom of expression. So, there you express yourself, but you're not trying to coerce
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,other people or force them to think your way. You're not trying to proselytize. You
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.61,0:28:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,stand there and you make a statement, like a mudra. A mudra makes a statement non-verbally,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.61,0:28:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not trying to coerce others by your statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.77,0:29:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The UN Security Council calibrates it 202. It's not a star in this whole thing, but
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.22,0:29:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it hangs on to integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.53,0:29:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 200 is integrity. 202 is the level of functionalism. Many government agencies calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.29,0:29:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it 202, many of them, the IRS. That's bureaucratic functionalism. And 202 is the waitress who
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.16,0:29:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,takes your order, but she doesn't smile and she don't remember you, and you don't feel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.27,0:29:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,compelled to return to that restaurant. I mean, I want somebody that says, hi, doc, the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.14,0:29:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.14,0:29:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.14,0:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of a liveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.14,0:29:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, 202 is you crawl up and you get a message. If you want so-and-so, press 1. If you want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.33,0:30:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so-and-so, press 2. You press 2, and now you've got a whole new menu. You go down to that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.91,0:30:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,menu, now press 6. So, it's functional, but it's not exactly warm, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.91,0:30:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the UN Security Council did not really warm the cockles of my heart, the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.20,0:30:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,way they handled this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.61,0:30:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.94,0:30:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we keep on examining this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.94,0:30:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we come to the revelation of some other phenomena in calibrating the energy levels
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.42,0:30:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.42,0:30:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.57,0:30:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm rewriting the Encyclopedia Britannica.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.33,0:30:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only up to M already.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.33,0:30:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, what were we going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.24,0:30:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.24,0:30:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What I wanted to do for these lectures, and I haven't gotten to it yet, is a map of the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.24,0:30:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.24,0:30:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I need, like, two slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.24,0:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One this side of the world and one slide this side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:30:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you calibrate the energy levels of the different continents, the different countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.26,0:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,different locations, and you'll find that much like human, I mean, much like animal
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.46,0:31:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,species, mankind, certain species tend to congregate together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.46,0:31:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find areas of the world, such as America, 431.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.46,0:31:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We take 431 for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.61,0:31:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,431 is amazingly high.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.00,0:31:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,431 means that you give reason priority over emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.00,0:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get down around the 200s and below 200, emotion is what counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.00,0:31:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred is more important than reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.00,0:31:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we're constrained by reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.08,0:31:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the gentleman's fault that I killed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.25,0:31:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's constrained by honesty and reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.53,0:31:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how deadly it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.98,0:31:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm a street fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.67,0:31:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a knife in the guy before he's ready for the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.67,0:31:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.38,0:31:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I play to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.38,0:32:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the street, you play to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.07,0:32:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This world is not run by Marquis of Queensberry rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.34,0:32:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get to, we left the Marquis of Queensberry rules up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.82,0:32:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are run by the Marquis of Queensberry rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.82,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They all went to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They all think that a thing is fair or not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.96,0:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In street fighting, whoever heard of fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.38,0:32:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the jungle, whoever heard of fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.89,0:32:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.89,0:32:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.89,0:32:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not fair to eat a little cub?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.40,0:32:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.40,0:32:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.75,0:32:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Different law.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.70,0:32:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the jungle is not the law of the Harvard rowing team.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.04,0:32:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.32,0:33:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So now if we turn the, if we shift the slide, which I haven't done yet, to other continents,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.38,0:33:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that whole continents calibrate incredibly low.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.48,0:33:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do Africa as a continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.57,0:33:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Africa as a continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.64,0:33:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 40, 50, 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.53,0:33:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole continent, 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.13,0:33:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're in the western continent, the places I've been, it's obvious at first sight that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.42,0:33:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate below 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.42,0:33:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The poverty in some areas of South America is absolutely stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.71,0:33:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,People talk about poverty in the United States, they haven't the slightest idea what poverty
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.09,0:33:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.82,0:33:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.82,0:33:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if we look at the Middle East, which historically has been at war for thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.52,0:34:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of years, and still is, now we get different calibrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.61,0:34:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Iran 185, Palestine 180, and Israel 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.14,0:34:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you got two 180s, both below integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.78,0:34:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They can pontificate all they want, but frankly, they calibrate 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.92,0:34:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.50,0:34:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace demonstrations, unfortunately, as I said, are too violent for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.75,0:34:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They only calibrate 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.75,0:34:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they represent force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything below 200 is force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.88,0:34:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to force others to see it your way, forced by intimidation, forced by demonstration,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.32,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Ku Klux Klan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,By demonstration, intimidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.26,0:34:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.53,0:34:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Turkey calibrates at 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.17,0:34:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a waffling country, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.17,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It waffles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Iraqi population is 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.21,0:34:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Iraq media is 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.21,0:35:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,France, who is in bed with these people, not surprisingly, calibrates their political position
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.92,0:35:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is also 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.92,0:35:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Syrian regime, at this point, is 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.19,0:35:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,These have made change over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.19,0:35:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple thousand years, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.78,0:35:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of mankind stood at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.65,0:35:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus, it was 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.03,0:35:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the Middle Ages, by the year 1200, 1420.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.03,0:35:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,By the year 1200, 1400.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.03,0:35:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,On up to the late 1980s, it was 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.03,0:35:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world was non-integrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.61,0:35:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Human history is not pleasant to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.53,0:35:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the storybooks of history, they pick out the flowers that survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.13,0:35:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mozart, the great heroes, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.03,0:35:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.96,0:36:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so unusual that it's in the history books.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.69,0:36:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was usual, it wouldn't be in the history books, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.88,0:36:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Syria, right now, 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.98,0:36:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Middle East in general, the whole Middle East as a region of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.98,0:36:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if we just do a world map, is 110.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.32,0:36:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,110.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.88,0:36:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you expect peace in a region that calibrates at 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.46,0:36:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Billification of the U.S. and the presidency has become a common political positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.46,0:36:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.53,0:36:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-integrist for reasons that we will get into later.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.53,0:36:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.53,0:36:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Saddam Hussein, God bless him, is 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.53,0:36:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Iraq military leaders are 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.71,0:36:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.71,0:37:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The real worry, the real worry in the world is jihad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.05,0:37:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the real worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.28,0:37:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It sets up the entire Muslim, Arabic, Middle East world against the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.53,0:37:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the real, that is the real worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.53,0:37:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it takes expression in Saddam Hussein.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.17,0:37:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And Iraq and bin Laden and various things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.03,0:37:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But to declare war against the rest of the world, then, is causing a deep division.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.38,0:37:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So jihad, in my view of it, is the most serious threat to peace in the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.57,0:37:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Islamic terrorists are just coming out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.57,0:37:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Taliban at 45 and bin Laden at 40 are the expression of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.13,0:37:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The energies of war, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.13,0:38:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The energies of war, we can look at fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.13,0:38:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that the enemy of war was falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.03,0:38:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.03,0:38:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemies of war are falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.40,0:38:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they become politically expressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.40,0:38:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The far left is Luciferic and the far right is Satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.50,0:38:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you have the display of non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.00,0:38:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luciferic then denies the sovereignty of God and seeks grandiose control over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do so, it distorts logic and truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.73,0:38:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the great enemy of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.09,0:38:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Trojan horse in the newest book I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.21,0:38:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you have read I?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.42,0:38:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so there's a certain familiarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.09,0:38:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trojan horse is to first present the lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.09,0:38:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I presented the lie to you before, this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.73,0:39:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of us had a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.71,0:39:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an honest, integrous gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.76,0:39:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.15,0:39:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw it happen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.88,0:39:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you saw a recapitulation of what led into World War I, World War II, and every other war.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.84,0:39:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up, you know, World War I has just ended and the veterans with battle shock and all were staggering around.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.19,0:39:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And World War II was now arising.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.19,0:39:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the obvious danger was ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.09,0:39:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The League of Nations was about as effective as the UN is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.09,0:39:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.09,0:40:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As this giant war machine built up, the greatest war machine the world has ever seen, built up right on the doorstep of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.09,0:40:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, there was all kinds of vociferous protest about peace and isolationism.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.92,0:40:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Lindbergh and Charlie Chaplin, all kinds of people got up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.65,0:40:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the actual diplomatic negotiation was handled by Neville Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.32,0:40:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.21,0:40:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain at the time calibrated at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.21,0:40:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So this morning we played the part of Hitler versus Neville Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.55,0:40:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was Hitler and he was Neville Chamberlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.86,0:40:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A gentleman who believed that I would be bound by a non-aggression treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.05,0:41:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So Neville Chamberlain went to meet with Hitler and they signed a non-aggression treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.17,0:41:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And he came back with a signed peace in our times.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.30,0:41:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Churchill saw that the truth of it was that this guy is a gangster, is going to laugh at a contract, and he's building up a giant war machine for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.94,0:41:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just for entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.30,0:41:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So Churchill was vilified as a war monger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.44,0:41:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,War monger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.44,0:41:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To be saying these kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.53,0:41:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The price, then, of the Trojan horse, of the fallacy of peace, which calibrated at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.01,0:41:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.73,0:41:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost 70 million lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.63,0:41:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Though political opinion is not all that innocent, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.94,0:42:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,70 million people dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.76,0:42:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.76,0:42:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their homes blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.21,0:42:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their country blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.21,0:42:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dresden, Cologne, all the magnificent beauty of medieval Europe destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.23,0:42:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The inability to tell a megalomaniac from a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.30,0:42:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Trojan horse, then, is the doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.05,0:42:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The doors to war are opened by a consciousness level of 180, which distorts truth because it's in denial about human nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.17,0:42:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's some kind of a schoolboy, Girl Scouts view of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.94,0:42:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just be nice to them, they will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.94,0:43:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In World War II, I was in dives in Shanghai waterfront.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.32,0:43:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And for entertainment, the war was just over, so suddenly there was no excitement going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.51,0:43:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the crew would go ashore and get into fights in various bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.90,0:43:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I had two cronies.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.50,0:43:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One was Big Red Hawkins, who played in for Pennsylvania.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.50,0:43:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He was about six foot five and weighed 290 pounds of solid muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.01,0:43:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A walking battering ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.30,0:43:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And red hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.13,0:43:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he quickly got angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.61,0:43:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The other guy was Jimmy Sanders, who was not all that tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.30,0:43:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jimmy Sanders was a bosun's mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.30,0:43:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was champion of the third fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.07,0:43:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.88,0:43:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I went on that ship, which is a minesweeper, the bosun says to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.17,0:43:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey shorty, you know how to box?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.36,0:44:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, gee, I took lessons with Richie Mitchell, who had been the former medium weight champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.48,0:44:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I told you this story before?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.48,0:44:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.53,0:44:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm a new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.53,0:44:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sent out on hazardous duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.98,0:44:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm the new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.98,0:44:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So Sanders says, well, let's do a couple of rounds in the gun tub.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.90,0:44:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I go into the gun tub with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.90,0:44:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We put on the gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.90,0:44:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And he knocked me cold with one sock in the jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.90,0:44:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One shot and I was cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.55,0:44:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they told me after, he was the champion of the third fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.51,0:44:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He was deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.55,0:44:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So fast you couldn't see him move.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.55,0:44:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a left jab that was so fast you didn't see it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.98,0:44:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you were grogged by his left jab.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.65,0:44:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he hit you with the upper right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.65,0:44:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This was so fast that you were jarred by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.65,0:45:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you were jarred, he hit you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.03,0:45:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he was something marvelous to watch, I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.28,0:45:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would go ashore, the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.28,0:45:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.13,0:45:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.86,0:45:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we go in these waterfront bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.36,0:45:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And my role was to, you know, we had a patch.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.36,0:45:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And being on a minesweep, you know, our whole crew was only 18 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.36,0:45:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all under 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.53,0:45:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.53,0:45:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we had a minesweep.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.53,0:45:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were in a big port there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.61,0:45:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were battleships that had 2,200 guys on them, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.61,0:45:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So they called us kiddie sailors.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.67,0:45:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd go into this bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.67,0:46:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would say, Shorty, go and talk to these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.09,0:46:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd go up to them, sit over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.09,0:46:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would sit over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.42,0:46:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon, a battleship sailor would look at me and say, hey, kiddie sailor.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.51,0:46:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, these two guys would come out of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.61,0:46:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd say, hey, are you insulting my friend here?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.61,0:46:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd push Shorty aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.61,0:46:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My job was to stay the hell out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.61,0:46:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Shorty, you go over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.92,0:46:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then pow, the whole place would be ripped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.44,0:46:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.53,0:46:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Stools flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.63,0:46:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Bodies flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.76,0:46:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirrors crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.61,0:46:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was murderous.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.61,0:46:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I only saw Jimmy Sanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.61,0:46:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He only got stopped once.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.61,0:46:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a guy up against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.61,0:46:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was about to cream him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.61,0:46:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the guy pulled out a French 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.61,0:46:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.30,0:46:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he knocked me out a couple other times, too, for one thing or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.63,0:47:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I went up to the top of the mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.63,0:47:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, don't look down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.63,0:47:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a fear of heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.63,0:47:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, don't look down, Shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.63,0:47:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I got all the way up to the top of the mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.76,0:47:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a paint bucket.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.76,0:47:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I made the mistake of looking down.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.76,0:47:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, the body froze to the mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.11,0:47:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.11,0:47:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My body did not respond to volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.11,0:47:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried very, very hard to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.11,0:47:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.26,0:47:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, Shorty, I'll have to cold cock you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.26,0:47:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope he comes in the bosun's chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.26,0:47:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So life in the arena of what's real is quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.26,0:47:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite different than the arena of political pretense.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.01,0:47:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Political pretense.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's deadly, then, is that that which is fallacious and presented as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.78,0:47:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,numbs you to the real truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.19,0:48:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And consequently, so the war starts with Lucifer distortion of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.71,0:48:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that opens the gates for the satanic, which is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.71,0:48:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the time is right, the satanic, which represents death, war, destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.71,0:48:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,rape, pillage, murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.71,0:48:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The rape of the then king was the satanic let loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.42,0:48:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The far left then is Luciferic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.42,0:48:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The far right is satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.73,0:48:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The door, nobody votes for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.73,0:48:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The satanic can't get elected.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.73,0:48:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't say, all you people, I want you to vote for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.38,0:48:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to vote for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.05,0:48:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The satanic doesn't win elections.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.05,0:48:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.76,0:48:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Luciferic sets the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.92,0:48:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the Trojan horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.92,0:48:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the door opens.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.92,0:48:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the satanic comes out with the guns and the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.92,0:49:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just want to see how war evolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.96,0:49:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is the case, if that is the case, if the prelude to all war is the distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.96,0:49:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth, if all war is set by falsehood, so the enemy of war, then, is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.78,0:49:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.73,0:49:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the essence of all the lectures we've given is that you really can't trust anything
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.73,0:49:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in this whole world at all, historically or currently, unless you calibrate this level
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.94,0:49:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.46,0:49:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.46,0:49:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because out of the humility, out of humility, you realize the nature of the mind is such
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.69,0:49:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that it cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.69,0:49:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot discover the cause of plague until you realize the beginning of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.65,0:50:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize, to begin with, that you do not know what the cause of plague is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.90,0:50:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you think it's overcrowding or night air coming into windows or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.17,0:50:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.17,0:50:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beginning of all great discovery is humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.09,0:50:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable of telling truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.09,0:50:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A politician doesn't become a great leader because he's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.34,0:50:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He becomes a great leader because he is extremely clever in how to persuade people and make
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.78,0:50:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,them sound logical and reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.21,0:50:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And what the great leader appeals to is your solar plexus and your spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.26,0:50:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler appealed to the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.05,0:51:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the course is always to right a wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.82,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind is led to slaughter by righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's righteous to undo the wrong of the Versailles Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.48,0:51:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been stopped very easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.48,0:51:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,By the French, when he invaded the Sudetenland, that would have been a snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.48,0:51:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have saved 70 million lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.46,0:51:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But that requires integrity and the capacity to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.46,0:51:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we cannot fault mankind, present or past, because it was blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.71,0:51:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't know the cause of plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.71,0:51:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was simply a bacillus carried by the rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.07,0:51:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rat flea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.28,0:51:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bacillus that's caused and is carried by the rat flea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.28,0:51:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rats don't cause the plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.28,0:51:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the flea doesn't cause the plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.80,0:52:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the plague bacillus carried by the flea.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.50,0:52:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start out saying, I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.42,0:52:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We only have one instrument.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.13,0:52:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We let you loose in this strange culture here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.13,0:52:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We let you out of the spacecraft from this other civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.90,0:52:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you only have one tool here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.90,0:52:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.09,0:52:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be way ahead of the game, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.34,0:52:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do the Encyclopedia Britannica.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.34,0:52:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize when you look at the Encyclopedia Britannica,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.34,0:52:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to let all of that stuff go to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.34,0:52:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.34,0:52:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All the belief systems, all the prevailing attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.55,0:52:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start out saying, I don't know anything about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.26,0:53:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it easier to let go of positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.32,0:53:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that I know and the idea that I must win,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.05,0:53:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that what I think my opinion must win,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.17,0:53:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whether people like it or not, is really the height of egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.11,0:53:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see in the current political world spectacular displays of egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.84,0:53:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom of speech means I can tell you what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.82,0:53:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond that is to exploit the freedom of speech
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.82,0:53:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and now to try to coerce others with moral indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.44,0:53:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The weapon that's really destroying our current American society
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.69,0:53:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and threatening the fabric of it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.09,0:53:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the business of moral indignation,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.61,0:53:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll get to later when we talk about business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.13,0:53:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.82,0:54:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a self-propagating industry, extremely well funded,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.21,0:54:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and its basic work is one of disquietude, complaints,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.59,0:54:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,grievances, moral indignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.17,0:54:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we satisfied that we know that they're seeing war and peace
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.17,0:54:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.23,0:54:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody have any doubts or questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.28,0:54:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody differs with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.69,0:54:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone wishes to have a duel about the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.21,0:54:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say the populace, the populace of this country at this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.34,0:54:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over so-and-so to get where it's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.84,0:54:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there we've seen endless decades
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.84,0:55:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of mutual provocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.03,0:55:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who wants peace gets assassinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.07,0:55:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to have a short regiment is to...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.32,0:55:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see mutual provocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.32,0:55:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I did write about that in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.48,0:55:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch the clash, you see the provocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.53,0:55:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because all this takes us into victim, victim, perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.90,0:55:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is tied in with a whole fallacious belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.90,0:55:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which prevails on our society,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.90,0:55:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do with perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.92,0:55:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you start a thing off is by playing the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.13,0:55:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you force the perpetrator to attack you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.80,0:56:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like suicide by police fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.38,0:56:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I force you now so that you can take the moral blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.48,0:56:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I feint that I have a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.65,0:56:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and now when the cop in self-defense shoots you,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.65,0:56:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the innocent victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.65,0:56:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an extremely non-integrist
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.07,0:56:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and rather malignant development in our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.55,0:56:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how it's based on cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.34,0:56:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at the entire world as if it was one human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.09,0:56:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,one human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the practice of medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.42,0:56:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to decide when you're going to operate on an appendix.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.42,0:56:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impending,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.42,0:56:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you wait too long,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.34,0:56:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the appendix will burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.61,0:56:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got a real problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.61,0:56:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've got an infection,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.61,0:56:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got peritonitis looking in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.61,0:57:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the physician's duty
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.55,0:57:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to anticipate an obvious process.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.55,0:57:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that the appendix is getting hotter and hotter
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.65,0:57:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and hotter and hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.65,0:57:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know that if you don't take action,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.86,0:57:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it will burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.13,0:57:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you will die of peritonitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.13,0:57:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.51,0:57:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To save the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.51,0:57:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to save the whole of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.80,0:57:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how far can a responsible person
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.80,0:57:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,let an appendix develop?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.80,0:57:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II, we saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.21,0:57:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,70 million was the death rate
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.57,0:57:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for failing to remove the appendix
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.15,0:57:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in a timely manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.26,0:57:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If the League of Nations was a physician,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.26,0:57:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd still be paying off his malpractice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.46,0:57:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't wait until it ruptures
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.78,0:57:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and costs 70 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.78,0:57:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or the death of the patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.26,0:57:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.26,0:58:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,my feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.07,0:58:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.07,0:58:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think about Bush?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My feeling about Bush is,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.67,0:58:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he states his position publicly
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.67,0:58:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.67,0:58:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask him,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.67,0:58:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what is his position?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.15,0:58:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,His position says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.40,0:58:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.40,0:58:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,my position is 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.40,0:58:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.88,0:58:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What is 460?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.82,0:58:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He tells you over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.65,0:58:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath of office
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.65,0:58:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with my hand on the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.01,0:58:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a man who's recovered from the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.17,0:58:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a man who's recovered
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.17,0:58:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from a fatal illness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.17,0:58:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.34,0:58:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason he favors
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.34,0:58:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually oriented recovery groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.30,0:58:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.30,0:58:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.30,0:58:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath on the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.55,0:58:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the obligation,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.55,0:58:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the oath of the President
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.55,0:58:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States of America,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.55,0:58:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is to defend its citizens
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.55,0:58:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,against all external aggressors.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.55,0:59:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My feeling is,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.34,0:59:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he is so profoundly committed to his oath,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.34,0:59:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll forego the next election,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.34,0:59:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll forego anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.57,0:59:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because he knows he's answerable to God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.57,0:59:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for the oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.57,0:59:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.38,0:59:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to confirm my intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.38,0:59:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My intuition is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.55,0:59:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.57,0:59:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Third step in AA,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.57,0:59:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you surrender your life to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.57,0:59:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're answerable only to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.57,0:59:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to the poll takers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.57,0:59:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to the politicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.57,0:59:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Having taken an oath of office
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.21,0:59:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and sworn in the name of God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.21,0:59:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to uphold the Constitution,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.21,0:59:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn't have any freedom to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.21,0:59:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I see his moral position.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.50,0:59:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,His moral position is he's pretty much stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.50,0:59:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the doctor in charge of the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.09,0:59:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're the doctor on call,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.09,0:59:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and they call you for a hot appendix
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.19,0:59:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at one in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.19,1:00:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you're it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.19,1:00:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as a physician,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.94,1:00:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you take an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.65,1:00:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many a time in my own career,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.65,1:00:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to decide,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.84,1:00:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,am I interested in my popularity
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.84,1:00:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.07,1:00:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Or am I answerable to God
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.07,1:00:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for fulfilling my duty to this patient?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.61,1:00:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of the techniques I used many years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.61,1:00:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,were not currently in favor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.69,1:00:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the medical establishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.19,1:00:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would look at the patient,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.19,1:00:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.19,1:00:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is my obligation to be popular with them?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.90,1:00:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Will I be answerable on my deathbed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.90,1:00:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for my popularity with my colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.01,1:00:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Or am I going to be confronted
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.30,1:00:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with the face of this man?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.65,1:00:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,God says,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.65,1:00:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I took an oath to serve this man,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.28,1:01:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is my oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.28,1:01:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Medicare regulations and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.38,1:01:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,aside the point.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.38,1:01:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very comical now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.30,1:01:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What the government calls HIPAA regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.61,1:01:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to protect the privacy of your patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.61,1:01:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.23,1:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've protected the privacy of my patient
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.23,1:01:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with my life since I started practicing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.23,1:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been done since the days of Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.23,1:01:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the government wants to come in and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.23,1:01:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,make it a law.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.23,1:01:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.23,1:01:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,where have these people been all this time?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.15,1:01:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Without integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.15,1:01:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot be a great practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.15,1:01:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So integrity then is the rule.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.69,1:01:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You follow your oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.69,1:01:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want to change that,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.05,1:01:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to disclaim that oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.05,1:01:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You turn in your medical license
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.05,1:01:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.07,1:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not abide by these rules anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.59,1:01:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't worship God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.61,1:02:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I worship the Medicare rules and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.44,1:02:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there's a difference between the two.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.44,1:02:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.03,1:02:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So one is integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.03,1:02:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as one states one's position
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.03,1:02:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and then is aligned with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.30,1:02:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.30,1:02:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make a statement
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.30,1:02:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is my position
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.30,1:02:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas actually you're devious
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.30,1:02:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and have a hidden agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.30,1:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the news media,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.00,1:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some of them that are controversial,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.00,1:02:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated them
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.15,1:02:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were higher than I thought they'd be
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.15,1:02:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because he states you right in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.15,1:02:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,States right in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.15,1:02:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my position.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.15,1:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And from that position,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.15,1:02:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how it looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.15,1:02:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how it looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.34,1:02:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's not pretending that he's in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.34,1:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's telling you,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.44,1:02:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a conservative.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.44,1:02:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up in the Midwest,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.44,1:02:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,conservative.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.13,1:02:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And from that viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.13,1:02:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,this is how it looks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.13,1:02:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.40,1:02:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that you're unbiased
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.51,1:02:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you're going to give
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.51,1:02:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolutely accurate accounting of the news
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.51,1:03:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and then give it a slant,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.51,1:03:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.51,1:03:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how some of the networks have gone down.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.51,1:03:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They've actually gone down in the last year
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.51,1:03:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because pretending to be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.94,1:03:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,objective where you're actually up to something
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.94,1:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's called a hidden agenda.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.28,1:03:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be integrous,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.34,1:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be as loony as you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.34,1:03:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is state that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.34,1:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with those positions,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.80,1:03:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they're practical or not is something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.80,1:03:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite easy to look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.57,1:03:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from a Buddhic monastic viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.57,1:03:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that no violence under any circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.63,1:03:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is allowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.78,1:03:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.78,1:03:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're living in a monastery.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.09,1:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're living on the streets
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.09,1:03:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of various cities in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.09,1:03:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll get you dead quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.65,1:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's not a lot of old Buddhist monks
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.65,1:03:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,hanging around in the streets.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.59,1:04:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.59,1:04:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to be a real proponent for peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.59,1:04:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have a piece of work again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.98,1:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to be a real one
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.98,1:04:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and not just one of these talkers,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.03,1:04:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then you become a champion of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.40,1:04:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth makes war impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.86,1:04:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When truth prevails,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.86,1:04:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,no war is possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.86,1:04:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So what can we do
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.63,1:04:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.63,1:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who is pro-peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.92,1:04:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which I presume most people here are?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As you grow in spiritual maturity,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.38,1:04:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you start out as the,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.38,1:04:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,ooh, isn't it all nice,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.38,1:05:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty flowers and blossoms.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.38,1:05:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sing hymns
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.38,1:05:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll pray for peace
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.90,1:05:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll tell him
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.90,1:05:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to be nice to him
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.90,1:05:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want him to be nice to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.90,1:05:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that'll work.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.90,1:05:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start out as spiritual innocents.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.90,1:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not aware of the downside of human nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.98,1:05:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we become adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.09,1:05:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We become adventurous.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.09,1:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to explore all the New Age fairs,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.09,1:05:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,get a million true psychic readings,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.09,1:05:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,throw the runes, the marbles,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.09,1:05:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the stones, the jacks,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.19,1:05:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.19,1:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw the cards,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.19,1:05:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,throw the picture card,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.19,1:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,get your fortune told,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.19,1:05:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we play around with that for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.51,1:05:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's the adolescent exploring the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.78,1:05:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, let's see the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.78,1:05:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.78,1:05:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what goes on?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.09,1:05:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course in our teaching we say
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.46,1:05:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,don't fool around with it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.46,1:05:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,stay away from it,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.46,1:05:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're naive,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.46,1:06:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.46,1:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't know what you're talking to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.46,1:06:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.42,1:06:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.42,1:06:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to control and persuade others.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.84,1:06:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.84,1:06:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,why would you want to persuade anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.84,1:06:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,about anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.84,1:06:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if anybody believes anything I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.48,1:06:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.48,1:06:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have one obligation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.48,1:06:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.48,1:06:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To speak of truth is I know it experientially
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.51,1:06:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and through research.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.57,1:06:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my only obligation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.17,1:06:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether anybody buys it is irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.17,1:06:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because on death's door I've done
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.21,1:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what I see I am to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.21,1:06:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My only obligation is to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.05,1:06:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only answerable to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.07,1:06:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So with that as a yardstick, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.07,1:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,one becomes,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.07,1:06:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,after the adolescent exploration,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.26,1:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,one then starts to become more involved
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.59,1:07:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in spirituality as a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.59,1:07:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You become sort of a champion of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.59,1:07:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we hit the level
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.13,1:07:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.13,1:07:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual warrior can be incredibly great
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.42,1:07:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or incredibly horrendous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.80,1:07:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The children down there with their hearts
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.11,1:07:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and flowers are no threat to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.11,1:07:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just wipe them out and dismiss them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.11,1:07:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The warrior now,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.25,1:07:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting enough power
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.25,1:07:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,due to dedication and inspiration,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.38,1:07:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be pretty dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.38,1:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the warrior now
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.71,1:07:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,can be either integrous or non-integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.71,1:07:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There are black warriors
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.46,1:07:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,just as there are white warriors
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.46,1:07:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking certain kinds of language.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.57,1:07:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who stand for peace, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.61,1:07:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and integrity, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.61,1:07:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be the champions of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.42,1:08:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And at some point in some lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.84,1:08:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to walk into the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.00,1:08:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a so what when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.30,1:08:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's ecstasy on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.30,1:08:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.40,1:08:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there are warriors that go in the other direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.40,1:08:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Jihad is the spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.52,1:08:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the dark side.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.38,1:08:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dangerous, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.53,1:08:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dangerous, religious wars
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.63,1:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are the most bloody of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.63,1:08:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are at 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.52,1:08:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jihad is 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.71,1:08:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very, very dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.73,1:08:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you think you're killing people for God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.73,1:08:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, the minute you add for God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.73,1:08:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now there are no restraints or limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.73,1:08:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,For God, you can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.77,1:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can kill millions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.93,1:09:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You can torture people to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.06,1:09:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can blow their heads off.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.09,1:09:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can operate on them without anesthesia
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.09,1:09:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,while they're still alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.76,1:09:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The most demented things are now
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.76,1:09:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,permissive, permissive.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.76,1:09:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where the danger lies in this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.46,1:09:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The danger is not Iraq and Saddam Hussein
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.50,1:09:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all those others.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.52,1:09:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are nobodies in the overall
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.52,1:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,historical evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.52,1:09:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here's what's going to hold up mankind right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.52,1:09:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know how they're going to get over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.90,1:09:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you polarize a good part of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.90,1:09:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in religious war,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.90,1:09:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,now you're going back in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.90,1:09:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, close to 2000 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.90,1:09:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the great religious wars of Islam,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.90,1:09:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.90,1:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,pitting Christians and others,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.90,1:09:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who's not a believer
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.90,1:09:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of whatever they believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.10,1:09:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.10,1:10:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is easily programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.93,1:10:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person who is really pro-peace, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.93,1:10:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a champion of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.26,1:10:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one guidepost to reach enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.26,1:10:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the core of all the lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.26,1:10:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and teachings and writings.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.26,1:10:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one thing you can trust,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.42,1:10:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is truth itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.42,1:10:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all you can trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.57,1:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All the good books,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.57,1:10:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can go to any spiritual bookshop,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.81,1:10:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's lined with good books.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.81,1:10:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lined with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.81,1:10:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Dozens of mantras and physical exercises.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.51,1:10:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathe in here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.51,1:10:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now run the energy down your left leg,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.51,1:10:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now go out your left nostril,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.51,1:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray to the angel,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.51,1:10:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and chant,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.51,1:10:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.51,1:10:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And they charge big bucks for those things,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.85,1:10:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the next level will cost you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.39,1:10:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,another couple hundred.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.39,1:10:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after that,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.39,1:10:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll cost you another 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.28,1:10:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.28,1:11:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There is absolutely no guidepost at all
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.97,1:11:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world we live in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.97,1:11:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with the human mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.97,1:11:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,other than to know
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.02,1:11:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute truth of something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.02,1:11:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.38,1:11:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.80,1:11:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.06,1:11:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,begins with humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.14,1:11:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is not capable
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.14,1:11:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of knowing truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.13,1:11:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we can't hate anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.13,1:11:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because if they get caught in a bad place,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.13,1:11:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,these jihad people are caught in a bad place.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.22,1:11:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're caught in the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.82,1:11:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get to heaven and God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.53,1:11:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,through your spleen?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.77,1:11:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get to someplace,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.77,1:11:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not celestial realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.42,1:11:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have names for the lower astral realms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.48,1:11:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So those go to the lower astral.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.48,1:11:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That which really denies God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.61,1:11:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and blasphemes the name of God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.61,1:12:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by labeling evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.22,1:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as divine.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.18,1:12:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate darkness
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.81,1:12:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is to label truth as falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.81,1:12:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to deny God and substitute the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.73,1:12:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not found through the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.27,1:12:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.27,1:12:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not found through the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.15,1:12:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,God is not found through the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.93,1:12:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot find God through hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.85,1:12:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,through killing people,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.10,1:12:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,through demonizing people,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.13,1:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by hating people.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.53,1:12:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So should we hate jihad people?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.82,1:12:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.82,1:12:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would we hate them?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.78,1:12:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hitler Youth under Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.78,1:12:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever watch any of those great documentaries
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.78,1:12:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on the History Channel?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.10,1:12:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up with a great compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.10,1:13:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for the German youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.10,1:13:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like the Boy Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.10,1:13:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They sat around the campfire
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.10,1:13:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and sang wonderful songs,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.10,1:13:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.10,1:13:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was patriotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.10,1:13:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was togetherness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.14,1:13:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.50,1:13:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you could form an image of yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.52,1:13:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as an adequate person.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.52,1:13:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was incredibly great.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.22,1:13:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that it worshipped
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.22,1:13:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a megalomaniac instead of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.22,1:13:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.78,1:13:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you watch how
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.78,1:13:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole culture was inculcated
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.78,1:13:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,into these belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.10,1:13:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't have thought otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.10,1:13:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had grown up in pre-Nazi Germany,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.10,1:13:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have become
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.10,1:13:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a follower of Adolf Hitler, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.36,1:13:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the savior of the German people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.36,1:13:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going to right the wrongs,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.36,1:13:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was the savior of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.15,1:13:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizing the existence of man
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.89,1:13:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.89,1:13:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.57,1:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,reason and a means
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.35,1:13:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to scream and shout
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.69,1:14:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to the crossroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.02,1:14:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.63,1:14:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an integralist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.63,1:14:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can be an integralist
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.65,1:14:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in your intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.02,1:14:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you are going
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.02,1:14:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.02,1:14:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And Krishna says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.02,1:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty there
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.44,1:14:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with that society
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.44,1:14:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is it was secular.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.69,1:14:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If they had acknowledged God
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.42,1:14:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the Great War, both sides ended up forgiving each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.75,1:14:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,German soldiers and American soldiers became close buddies after the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.31,1:14:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody transcended the positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.19,1:14:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw each other just as other human beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.30,1:14:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to respect the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.77,1:14:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, here's a guy who's willing to give his life for his country.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.07,1:14:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I've got to salute that guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.14,1:14:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I may think his plane is going in the wrong direction, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.00,1:14:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, his intention was valorous, was it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.78,1:15:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what more can you ask of a person?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.07,1:15:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You give up your life for your country.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.22,1:15:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So each person then, as Christ said, and as the Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.64,1:15:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody, whoever, anybody has said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.06,1:15:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that we end up forgiving people and we're compassionate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.56,1:15:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because we see the limitation of human ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.57,1:15:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic to the whole structure of the human psyche
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.65,1:15:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is the incapacity to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.84,1:15:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that reason, we are willing to...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.77,1:15:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive anyone, no matter how,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.77,1:15:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,far from the truth they may appear to us to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.60,1:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we get to the level of the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.50,1:15:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Bush is in a spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.22,1:15:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Powell is more to the heart of the spiritual warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.60,1:15:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is carrying forth, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.89,1:15:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as he sees it, his Christian duty,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.00,1:16:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,based on his oath of office, his integrity to himself
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.43,1:16:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and to his fellow Americans.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.88,1:16:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so one can have an opinion about it one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.09,1:16:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But our job is not to have an opinion about things.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.64,1:16:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Our job is to try and avoid opinions.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.17,1:16:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if the way to peace is through truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.55,1:16:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then we have to know what truth is.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.09,1:16:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At first observation, we noticed that 78% of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.18,1:16:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is against truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.01,1:16:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have our calibrated levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.40,1:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,From here up, the commitment is the truth of increasing degrees.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.28,1:16:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From here down,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.88,1:16:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's to falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.97,1:16:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.97,1:16:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you want peace in a society, in a world,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.02,1:16:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in which close to 80% of the people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.52,1:16:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,would rather have anything but peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.17,1:16:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.35,1:17:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it's more important to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.78,1:17:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.46,1:17:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Celebrities get up there, make idiots out of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.52,1:17:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's their big ego wanting to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.30,1:17:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, people like that can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.93,1:17:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People would rather be right, even if it costs them their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.65,1:17:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't care anything at all about truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.38,1:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It cares about winning and being right at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.69,1:17:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Be right at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.50,1:17:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's have the calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.72,1:17:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're going to see where does mankind go then.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.11,1:17:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So first of all, only 20% of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.34,1:17:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,even gets to the opening doors to truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.00,1:18:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you're committed to integrity greater than gain,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.89,1:18:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a solar plexus, winning solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.22,1:18:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you go down then, you go down through the pride,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.67,1:18:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,arrogance, greed, fear, all the way down.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.47,1:18:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Vindictiveness, hatred, polarization.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.72,1:18:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been talking today mainly about the Middle East phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.43,1:18:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's in today's current news.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.13,1:18:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is spirituality and the world, so I feel obligated to.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.28,1:18:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fulfill that title.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.25,1:18:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what we've been looking at is the high side of life, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.52,1:18:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle East calibrates at what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.03,1:18:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say, 140 or, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.52,1:18:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.55,1:19:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.71,1:19:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Middle East then is a region that calibrates at 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.14,1:19:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A festering appendix.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.82,1:19:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision of the government had to be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.68,1:19:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,how long should we wait for the appendix?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.18,1:19:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we wait until it erupts?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.10,1:19:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, how long should we wait?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.57,1:19:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what happened in World War II, World War I.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.57,1:19:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should we try and nip it in the bud?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.68,1:19:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it or not, you've got to operate.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.68,1:19:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's what his practical,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.68,1:19:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,pragmatic decision was.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.25,1:19:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.25,1:19:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how the world looks at 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.25,1:19:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We look at Israel and Palestine, calibrate 180,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.53,1:19:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.85,1:19:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that that war goes on and on and on.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.85,1:19:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going on since I've been on the planet, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.85,1:19:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens if we look at the really bad part of the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.67,1:19:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we look at Africa?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.23,1:20:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rwanda.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.15,1:20:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Civil war has been going on there for decades.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.15,1:20:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.N. has the slightest interest
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.15,1:20:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that they slaughter each other,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.15,1:20:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cut each other's legs off,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.53,1:20:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,torture each other to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.77,1:20:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The main way of death in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.89,1:20:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which is at war all the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.89,1:20:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is to hack people in small pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.89,1:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.52,1:20:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we take sort of a calm, detached look at the planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.81,1:20:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.39,1:20:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,probably for karmic reasons,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.39,1:20:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,certain levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.48,1:20:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,seem to congregate
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.48,1:20:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and get themselves born
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.48,1:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in various regions around the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.48,1:20:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.84,1:20:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The elephant herds don't hang out in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.84,1:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.97,1:20:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's been human nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.97,1:20:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The way of animal life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.97,1:21:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,for 40 million years or more,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.97,1:21:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,400 million years,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.06,1:21:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is that groups tend to congregate
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.06,1:21:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in certain places on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.06,1:21:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the darkest place
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.35,1:21:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is really Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.35,1:21:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Middle East is quite a bit advanced
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.35,1:21:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from where Africa is.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.64,1:21:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.85,1:21:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what percent of children die
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.85,1:21:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,before age two or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.85,1:21:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They do survive. They probably have AIDS.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.85,1:21:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's doubtful that they'll live long enough
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.85,1:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to die of malnutrition.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.85,1:21:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so staggering
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.23,1:21:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that it never hits the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.23,1:21:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see television commercials
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.61,1:21:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or television documentaries
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.85,1:21:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on current life
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.85,1:21:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.85,1:21:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably couldn't get on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.64,1:21:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just too horrendous to look at.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.64,1:21:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can look at 110.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.77,1:21:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,110 makes great news.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.35,1:21:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the media's going to do
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.35,1:21:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when the war is finally over
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.51,1:21:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and cleaned up.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.51,1:22:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got, what's her name,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.80,1:22:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Peterson.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.53,1:22:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That saved him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.63,1:22:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The war came to an end
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.63,1:22:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and happily they discovered Peterson's body
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.63,1:22:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just in time to save the news media.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.63,1:22:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we going to talk about now?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.63,1:22:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They squeezed every last little bit
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.63,1:22:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of news out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.92,1:22:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to get a kick out of them
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.92,1:22:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because they'll tell you something that happened
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.92,1:22:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they'll tell you what they just told you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.92,1:22:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they'll tell you what they just told you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.92,1:22:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they told you it's a repetition.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.92,1:22:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really squeezing the last
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.92,1:22:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,lemon out of the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.65,1:22:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we call
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.65,1:22:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,juicing a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.17,1:22:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Juicing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.00,1:22:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that suits
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.67,1:22:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego better than war
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.96,1:22:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to really juice it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.59,1:22:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The third chapter,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.59,1:22:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was chapter four
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.59,1:22:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of the current book I put out
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.61,1:22:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,took the longest to write
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.61,1:22:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.61,1:23:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and society.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.06,1:23:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How to look at society
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.06,1:23:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and see it as a projection of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.10,1:23:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so that like a student
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.10,1:23:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can impersonally and detachedly
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.10,1:23:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,just study it as a phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.10,1:23:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And a great deal of what we've done
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.26,1:23:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in these classes
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.26,1:23:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is to just study
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.26,1:23:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior and its expression throughout history
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.26,1:23:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from a somewhat detached
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.46,1:23:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,objective view
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.46,1:23:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,just as we tried to diagnose
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.38,1:23:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the war this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.85,1:23:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we see is an endless game
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.85,1:23:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,an endless game
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.85,1:23:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the players in the game
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.85,1:23:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the different moves
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.85,1:23:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can make.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.03,1:23:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the position I played with the gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.03,1:23:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the advantage
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.53,1:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a street fighter
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.60,1:23:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that means I can hit you from any direction
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.60,1:23:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I can move in any direction
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.30,1:23:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.59,1:24:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.96,1:24:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dead already
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.96,1:24:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,before the fight starts
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.96,1:24:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't got a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.93,1:24:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have unlimited movement.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.93,1:24:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you look at the chessboard of life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.28,1:24:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a unique piece
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.47,1:24:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can move in any direction
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.47,1:24:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,any time I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.68,1:24:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This piece over here
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.31,1:24:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the gentleman can only move
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.31,1:24:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in this way or this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.38,1:24:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,See how the gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.81,1:24:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is already limited?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.34,1:24:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the religionist, the bishop
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.65,1:24:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,he can't move this way and this way
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.65,1:24:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he can only move this way and this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.03,1:24:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the limitation of motion
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.03,1:24:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the limitation of options
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.03,1:24:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,goes down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.72,1:24:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we watch social phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.72,1:24:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is the ego's game board
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.72,1:25:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in which it plays
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.26,1:25:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these different players
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.68,1:25:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,each one you have to see
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.68,1:25:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what are his options, what's his upside
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.68,1:25:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what's his downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.25,1:25:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is somebody who calibrates at 130
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.25,1:25:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,going to honor
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.60,1:25:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a contract?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.01,1:25:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler signed the non-aggression
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.56,1:25:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,treaty with
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.65,1:25:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.10,1:25:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,his intention was to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.09,1:25:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,After they signed
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.42,1:25:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.02,1:25:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.02,1:25:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was a stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.38,1:25:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought he was a stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.38,1:25:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about war man
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.94,1:25:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about survival
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.94,1:26:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about death
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.34,1:26:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and this idiot thinks I want to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.34,1:26:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,honor a piece of paper?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.98,1:26:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how Lindbergh
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.98,1:26:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that ilk
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.92,1:26:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to the blindness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.17,1:26:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's bring in the Trojan horse
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.17,1:26:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just a horse
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.48,1:26:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,looks peaceful
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.61,1:26:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and out comes the Jihad
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.97,1:26:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spiritual warrior then
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.97,1:26:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,has to give up naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.97,1:26:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual maiden
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.67,1:26:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,can go around saying
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.67,1:26:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,oh isn't that wonderful
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.73,1:26:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have hearts and flowers
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.73,1:26:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll sing songs
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.89,1:26:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and wear long robes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.19,1:26:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the world doesn't change
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.19,1:26:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have enough power
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.50,1:26:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so the spiritual warrior now
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.50,1:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.32,1:27:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,has to give up naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.10,1:27:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I warned you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.10,1:27:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as spiritual work takes you higher and higher
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.22,1:27:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you get into the 500's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.73,1:27:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the 500's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.73,1:27:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,one can only see innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.73,1:27:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and love
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.85,1:27:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all you can see there
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.85,1:27:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.97,1:27:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.10,1:27:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear that there could be
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.10,1:27:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else out there
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.43,1:27:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is not thinkable
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.43,1:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so the downside of the 500's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.43,1:27:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the bliss state
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.43,1:27:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is to close your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.59,1:27:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.59,1:27:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is not a celestial realm
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.02,1:27:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we're living in
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.02,1:27:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so the vulnerability then
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.31,1:27:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about by naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.31,1:27:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.31,1:27:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you can turn that off for a second
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.31,1:27:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes about by naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.97,1:27:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wishful thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.97,1:28:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,aspirant then has to go through
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.97,1:28:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,some difficult times
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.03,1:28:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and letting go of these illusions
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.03,1:28:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go of these illusions
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.73,1:28:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.28,1:28:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,be a champion of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.67,1:28:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to do things that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.67,1:28:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to the spiritual maiden
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.67,1:28:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,sound just awful
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.67,1:28:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, how could you do that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.67,1:28:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,how could you take a knife
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.09,1:28:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and cut open a person's belly
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.09,1:28:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you do
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.97,1:28:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to save a life
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.97,1:28:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta cut open the belly
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.97,1:28:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't clamp them off
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.09,1:28:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they exsanguinate
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.38,1:28:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,right on the table
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.47,1:28:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or they die of shock
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.27,1:28:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't they die of peritonitis
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.27,1:28:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so like the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.27,1:28:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,like the physician, like the surgeon
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.27,1:28:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then the spiritual warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.30,1:28:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,reaches the point
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.30,1:28:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,where you have to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.30,1:28:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are areas
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.72,1:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,where in almost a surgical precision
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.72,1:29:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be willing to transcend certain illusions
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.72,1:29:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they seem painful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.86,1:29:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but let them go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.35,1:29:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach spiritual maturity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.35,1:29:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by hanging out
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.35,1:29:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.35,1:29:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,naivete is one thing
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.38,1:29:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,maturity is another
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.89,1:29:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we become more realistic
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.89,1:29:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so we stand for then
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.89,1:29:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the dominance of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.89,1:29:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth as the way
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.89,1:29:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to God, the way to realization
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.89,1:29:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the self, the way to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.89,1:29:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to truth then
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.43,1:29:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is to let go of positionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.64,1:29:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,war and peace are neither good nor bad
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.64,1:29:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't say that to a normal
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.65,1:29:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,audience
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.65,1:29:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think about
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.65,1:29:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or feel about war and peace
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.93,1:29:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you want me to be honest
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.10,1:30:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all the same to me
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.63,1:30:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any difference one way or the other
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.06,1:30:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.06,1:30:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because beyond perception
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.06,1:30:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have any particular reality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.06,1:30:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,nor do they have any moral loading
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.06,1:30:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ethical loading of goodness and badness
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.02,1:30:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the reality which is this instant right now
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.50,1:30:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no war, no peace
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.50,1:30:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no anything else
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.50,1:30:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,those are all programs and stories
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.55,1:30:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you know whether you go out of
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.55,1:30:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a body like this bang
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.55,1:30:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or you go out
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.06,1:30:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell is the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.06,1:30:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people who have survived heart attacks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.00,1:30:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people who have had near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.00,1:30:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know what I am talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.00,1:30:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all the same folks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.65,1:30:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,happily I had a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.65,1:30:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in teenage
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.61,1:30:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,during the war death didn't mean anything at all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.61,1:31:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there is this mind
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.55,1:31:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with what you would call sticking out
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.55,1:31:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,like this and starting to bump against
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.55,1:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the star of our ship you know
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.55,1:31:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are going to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.55,1:31:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,any second you are going to just go up with
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.61,1:31:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,this fine thing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.51,1:31:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so all I am worried about is it is going to scratch
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.51,1:31:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the paint on the side of the thing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.51,1:31:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and blow us all the kingdom come
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.51,1:31:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.51,1:31:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,hey man get a boat hook and help me will you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.63,1:31:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,no fear of death at all
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.89,1:31:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so it is comical
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.89,1:31:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you get outside of this instant
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.50,1:31:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have fear
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.50,1:31:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I still see a few old patients that I have seen for umpteen years
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.21,1:31:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they are too old
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.21,1:31:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they slowly die off so I just figure
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.21,1:31:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I will just wait
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.90,1:31:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they are all as old as I am
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.90,1:31:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.32,1:31:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those that are walking in one banana peel
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.32,1:32:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them look call me for the next appointment
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.71,1:32:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so one of them
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.86,1:32:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of course I adore them all
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.86,1:32:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that is why I don't chuck them all
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.22,1:32:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I adore them
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.22,1:32:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,this old guy is sitting there
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.38,1:32:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has got this oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.38,1:32:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he has got his oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.38,1:32:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is older than nails older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.38,1:32:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,she calls me older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.38,1:32:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,deficit post and older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.38,1:32:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,she tells all the nurses
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.57,1:32:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so anyway he is older than dirt
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.57,1:32:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and he comes in and he has got his oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.57,1:32:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has got this thing around his nose
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.64,1:32:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sits down and he says
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.64,1:32:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you got a light
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.64,1:32:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.64,1:32:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he put his cigarette in his mouth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.64,1:32:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.64,1:32:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are we going to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.64,1:32:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he says I don't think so
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.64,1:32:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said ok
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.78,1:32:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't think so
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.78,1:32:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose you should shut off the oxygen before hand
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.10,1:33:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sure it has got a
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.10,1:33:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,got a warning on the tank
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.61,1:33:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I said what does it say on the tank
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.14,1:33:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he says I don't know I never read it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.14,1:33:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the manufacturer I am sure doesn't want to get sued
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.92,1:33:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if we blow each other up
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.92,1:33:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is that living in the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.17,1:33:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.17,1:33:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it really didn't make any difference
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.17,1:33:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if we both went sky high
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.17,1:33:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we went sky high
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.61,1:33:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you got to get out of here somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.61,1:33:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you want it slow and horrid
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.61,1:33:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.35,1:33:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so to die for one's cause
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.35,1:33:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.50,1:33:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of course the hero of the war
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.50,1:33:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is that young lady who got captured
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.56,1:33:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and beat up
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.72,1:33:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so she stands for something
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.14,1:33:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.18,1:33:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,embedded in the core of America
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.18,1:34:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.89,1:34:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,warrior but not just a warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.89,1:34:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a warrior with commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.89,1:34:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.98,1:34:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,between the killer and the warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.98,1:34:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the warrior is doing it for a principle
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.98,1:34:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,doing it for a cause
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.25,1:34:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,doing it for something greater than themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.25,1:34:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and in World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.65,1:34:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater than oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.65,1:34:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was not just one's country and all
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.65,1:34:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course everybody wanted to win
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.65,1:34:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was more a loyalty to one's
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.65,1:34:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,shipmates
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.97,1:34:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the loyalty to one's shipmates
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.97,1:34:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.18,1:34:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous core
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.61,1:34:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if that mind blew up
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.17,1:34:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we blew up
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.64,1:34:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but that didn't stop somebody else
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.64,1:34:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from coming over and helping
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.77,1:34:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see in the midst of war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.77,1:34:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that which
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.77,1:34:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we would think would be highly
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.77,1:34:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know not really a very spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.77,1:34:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of a place
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.93,1:35:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the midst of war is sacred indeed
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.93,1:35:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the midst of war
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.51,1:35:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is sacred
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.40,1:35:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the midst of war is where a bonding goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.40,1:35:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.40,1:35:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of those shipmates
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.93,1:35:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sixty years ago or whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.34,1:35:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,those that still
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.34,1:35:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,remain
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.38,1:35:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are the same as they had always
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.38,1:35:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,been and I remember when they
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.38,1:35:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,called me up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.60,1:35:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they located each other
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.60,1:35:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,after fifty or sixty years
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.89,1:35:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody started to cry
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.89,1:35:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you hear this person's voice
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.89,1:35:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they say this is so and so
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.89,1:35:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly the tears would come up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.02,1:35:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that veterans of World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.17,1:35:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're interviewed about the war
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.17,1:35:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see that patriotism is of the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.86,1:35:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to not love your country
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.86,1:35:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,means to be dead
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.47,1:35:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if you cannot love the source
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.47,1:35:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of your survival
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.80,1:36:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,my father and my mother
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.80,1:36:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean biologic
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.80,1:36:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,those two people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.80,1:36:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to honor your heritage
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.38,1:36:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.38,1:36:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is now expressing itself
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.69,1:36:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the karmic upside of the human
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.69,1:36:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you've inherited
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.69,1:36:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.94,1:36:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.10,1:36:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to share
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.10,1:36:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.23,1:36:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgive each other when the chips are down
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.23,1:36:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when World War II is over
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.23,1:36:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.90,1:36:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive each other
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.85,1:36:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what could he do except do his best
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.85,1:36:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Weimar people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.72,1:36:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so we saw the basic integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.72,1:36:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and because we saw the ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.72,1:36:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,under the integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.72,1:36:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,where he willingly forgave each other
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.14,1:36:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have any resentment
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.88,1:37:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,left about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.81,1:37:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,about any fact of war
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.81,1:37:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so in the end compassion then
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.06,1:37:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,takes us beyond war and peace
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.10,1:37:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings us to the awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.10,1:37:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of our reality
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.77,1:37:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that all that goes on there
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.77,1:37:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that brings itself out there
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.77,1:37:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as human society
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.06,1:37:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,can't help be what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.06,1:37:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment it's being what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.06,1:37:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if it could be something else
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.06,1:37:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.10,1:37:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that it isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.10,1:37:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,means it can't
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.14,1:37:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if the person with an IQ of 90
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.14,1:37:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,could get straight hundreds
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.14,1:37:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in school he would
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.69,1:37:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with an IQ of 90
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.69,1:37:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you're lucky to get straight C's
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.97,1:37:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's all we expect of them
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.97,1:37:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.97,1:37:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on this planet
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.97,1:37:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we share a common commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.27,1:37:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of being a human
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.27,1:37:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is staggering
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.65,1:38:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,just be a human
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.90,1:38:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I honor and respect
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.90,1:38:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,any human being that walks this planet
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.03,1:38:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because to be a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.03,1:38:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is extraordinarily difficult
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.03,1:38:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely painful
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.03,1:38:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely challenging
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.10,1:38:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,uncertain at every second
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.57,1:38:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,one second of inattention
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.57,1:38:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and your car rolls over and you're dead
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.57,1:38:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so we all live one second from death
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.22,1:38:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,more people have died on the highways in Arizona
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.22,1:38:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,than have died in Iraq
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.22,1:38:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,this last month
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.22,1:38:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,since the time the war's been on
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.22,1:38:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,more people have been killed on the highway
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.22,1:38:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the US military
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.60,1:38:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not dramatic
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.60,1:38:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,see how we just accept
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.60,1:38:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,well death by automobile
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.60,1:38:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a big story
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.82,1:38:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 people die a year
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.82,1:38:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in automobile deaths
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.82,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the excitement
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the drama
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.82,1:38:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where's the parades
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.89,1:38:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a lot of different politicians out there
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.89,1:39:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with a big make wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.53,1:39:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.77,1:39:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the tendency of the ego then is to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.77,1:39:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,take a position
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.93,1:39:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then dramatize it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.93,1:39:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then put a lot of energy in it
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.93,1:39:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets polarized against people who think differently
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.93,1:39:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,than you do
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.61,1:39:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the positions that people represent then
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.61,1:39:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about the war
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.61,1:39:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are reflective of their level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.71,1:39:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we need a level of consciousness back again
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.40,1:39:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,alright we said 80% of the people live
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.40,1:39:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,below here
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.85,1:39:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so if we calibrate people's level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.85,1:39:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.85,1:39:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not reflecting reality
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.85,1:39:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they're reflecting their own level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.85,1:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,people who live down here
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.50,1:39:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.22,1:39:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,these people come out of gain
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.55,1:39:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to reconstruct Iraq now
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.55,1:39:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see all the bottom feeders coming in
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.55,1:40:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with those contracts
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.55,1:40:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,get them contracts
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.55,1:40:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when the fight is going on
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.55,1:40:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll disappear
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.55,1:40:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's time to start
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.55,1:40:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're missing the pumps
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.55,1:40:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's out there with their hands out
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.55,1:40:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so there you got the solar plexus in greed
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.55,1:40:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how pride plays into the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.55,1:40:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how rage, anger
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.55,1:40:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how fear drives people
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.55,1:40:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then we have the courageous
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.64,1:40:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.64,1:40:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,really make the headlines
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.64,1:40:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that girl will be a hero forever
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.82,1:40:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then you get into neutrality
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.82,1:40:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond it all
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.69,1:40:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the position I gave to you before
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.50,1:40:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like neutrality
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.50,1:40:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay if we have peace, it's okay if we have war, don't bother me
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.19,1:40:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the detachment
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.19,1:40:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then the willingness to enter in
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.19,1:40:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and own the bottom side of it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.19,1:40:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then the acceptance that this is human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.19,1:40:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we're seeing is human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.19,1:40:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing itself out there on the game board
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.19,1:40:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.57,1:40:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at this point
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.57,1:41:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see the intellect and reason
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.64,1:41:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect and reason is the doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.64,1:41:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it says
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.64,1:41:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how far can we let this appendix go
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.64,1:41:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,before we do something
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.97,1:41:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see love surpassing all of it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.06,1:41:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that love
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.06,1:41:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is unlimited
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.38,1:41:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,unlimited love at 540
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.38,1:41:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is rare, rare
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.38,1:41:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to love everybody no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.38,1:41:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,can we feel sorry for Ben Loudon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.57,1:41:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these people
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.14,1:41:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pathetic isn't it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.14,1:41:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in hating somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.43,1:41:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that is so weird
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.96,1:41:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the name of that dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.68,1:41:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.17,1:41:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if we can find out
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.28,1:41:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,my friend the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.61,1:41:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 40
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.93,1:41:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have permission
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.48,1:41:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,45
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.28,1:42:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Komodo dragon calibrates about 40
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.92,1:42:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can you believe a guy going in there with his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.92,1:42:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to make nice with the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.88,1:42:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he did it so help me
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.67,1:42:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he took his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.60,1:42:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and he thought he was tame
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.93,1:42:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw the game we started with
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.06,1:42:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,well I was the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.64,1:42:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was the movie star
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.64,1:42:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or the husband of the movie star remember him
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.64,1:42:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,takes his shoes off
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.64,1:42:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and hangs out with the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.64,1:42:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's still living
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.64,1:42:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond imagination
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.93,1:42:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,oh let's have the war and peace
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.93,1:42:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,back again now that we have the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.93,1:42:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we really should have Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.65,1:42:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on there for contrast
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.57,1:42:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so help me God there is a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.57,1:42:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates the same as the Komodo dragon
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.57,1:42:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we should really
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.85,1:42:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,enter into peace negotiations
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.85,1:43:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with him don't you think
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.85,1:43:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I will invite him to a duel
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.98,1:43:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,me and Ben Loudon
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.85,1:43:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will demonstrate
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.98,1:43:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how to do that
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.23,1:43:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,gentlemen would you like to come up again
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.23,1:43:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have another duel
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.72,1:43:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.06,1:43:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have a break
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.35,1:43:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have a short break and then we'll resume
